HEADWORD: Catenary
<hw>Cat"e*na*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<er>Catenaries</er> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The
curve formed by a rope or chain of uniform density and perfect
flexibility, hanging freely between two points of suspension, not in the
same vertical line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

